<text id="WB_KL-87">
  <metadata>
            <title>"Tattoos"</title>
            <author>Julia <alph>Starritt</alph></author>
            <date>1957</date>
            <publication>William Bright, <em>The Karok Language</em> (1957), pp. 300-301, Text 87</publication>
        </metadata>
        <data>
            <paragraph>
                <s>
                    <kar>
                        <w gl="the Indian woman"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="506">'arara</m><m id="656">'asiktávaan</m></w>
                        <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
			<w><m id="3136">ishváak</m></w>
			<w gl="it was tattooed"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="6015">thúkinh</m><m id="168">ahi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>.
                  </kar>
                    <eng>The Indian women were tattooed on the chin.</eng>
                </s>
                <s>
                    <kar>
                        <w><m id="4108">kuyráak</m></w>
			<w gl="it runs down in lines"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="5342">sasip</m><m id="6239">úniih</m><m id="6380">va</m></w>
			<w><m id="7097">yítha</m></w>
			<w><m id="104">achipyâach</m></w>
			<w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
			<w><m id="6767">xákararih</m></w>. 
		    </kar>
                    <eng>There were three stripes running down, one right in the middle and (two) on each side.</eng>
                </s>
		<s>
                    <kar>
                        <w><m id="1361">hâari</m></w>
			<w gl="wide ones"><m id="6087">tírih</m><m id="5200">shas</m></w>
			<w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
			<w><m id="1361">hâari</m></w>
			<w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
			<w><m id="6156">tûupichas</m></w>
			<w><m id="4106">kuynákmahich</m></w>
			<w gl="it runs down in lines"><m id="4408">p</m><m id="6175">oo</m><m id="5342">sasip</m><m id="6239">úniih</m><m id="6380">va</m></w>. 
		    </kar>
                    <eng>Sometimes they were wide and sometimes they were narrow, and sometimes they were each (composed of) three little ones running down.</eng>
                </s>
	    </paragraph>
	    <paragraph>
	      <s>
		<kar>
		  <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
		  <w gl="sharp stone"><m id="583">asa</m><m id="7044">yátha</m></w>
		  <w><m id="4281">mûuk</m></w>
		  <w gl="they marked it"><m id="4408">pa</m><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="2304">ikxúrik</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>.
		</kar>
		<eng>And they made the design with a sharp stone.</eng>
	      </s>
	      <s>
		<kar>
		  <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
		  <w><m id="368">amyiv</m></w>
		  <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
		  <w><m id="779">athkúrit</m></w>
		  <w><m id="5506">ta</m></w>
		  <w gl="they mixed"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="3602">íyshar</m></w>,
		  <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
		  <w><m id="6383">vaa</m></w>
		  <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
		  <w gl="they rubbed it"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="3642">iyvúruk</m></w>
		  <w gl="on the tattoo"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="6016">thúkinh</m><m id="232">ak</m></w>.
		</kar>
		<eng>Then they mixed soot and grease, and they rubbed it on the tattoo.</eng>
	      </s>
	      <s>
		<kar>
		  <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
		  <w gl="when it healed"><m id="4408">pa</m><m id="5506">t</m><m id="6175">u</m><m id="543">'aráriihkanha</m><m id="1358">ak</m></w>
		  <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
		  <w gl="not black"><m id="5082">pu</m><m id="2242">'ikxáramkunish</m><m id="1371">hara</m></w>,
		  <w><m id="3999">kúnish</m></w>
		  <w><m id="343">ámkuufkunish</m></w>. 
		</kar>
		<eng>And when it healed, it was not black, it was sort of blue.</eng>
	      </s>
	    </paragraph>
	    <paragraph>
	      <s>
		<kar>
		  <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
		  <w gl="here"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="4385">'ôok</m></w>
		  <w gl="its people"><m id="6376">va</m><m id="506">'áraar</m><m id="584">as</m></w>
		  <w gl="their face"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="4264">mukún</m><m id="67">'aav</m></w>
		  <w gl="they didn't tattoo"><m id="5082">p</m><m id="6175">u</m><m id="6015">thúkinhi</m><m id="6035">ti</m><m id="1371">hara</m></w>. 
		</kar>
		<eng>And the Indians here didn't tattoo their faces (above the chin).</eng>
	      </s>
	      <s>
		<kar>
		  <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
		  <w><m id="4725">páy nanuxákarari</m></w>
		  <w><m id="3809">kích</m></w>
		  <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
		  <w><m id="6383">vaa</m></w>
		  <w gl="they did"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="4015">kupitih</m></w>. 
		</kar>
		<eng>Only ones outside of our country did that.*</eng>
	      </s>
	      <note>*The informant later corrected herself, saying that the Karok sometimes made small marks just above each corner of the mouth.</note>
	    </paragraph>
	</data>
</text>
